EXPOSED.Definition: to submit or make accessible to a particular action or influence

STAND-UP.Definition: performed in, performing in, or requiring a standing position especially: of, relating to, performing, or being a monologue of jokes, gags, or satirical comments delivered usually while standing alone on a stage or in front of a camera

COMEDIAN.Definition: a person whose job is to make people laugh by telling jokes and funny stories or by copying the behavior or speech of famous people

HUMBLE.Definition: poor or of a low social rank

CAREER.Definition: the job or series of jobs that you do during your working life, especially if you continue to get better jobs and earn more money

ENTERTAINER.Definition: someone whose job is to entertain people by singing, telling jokes, etc.

CLIP.Definition: a short part of a movie or television program

Y'ALL.Definition: short for 'you all'; used to address a group of people that you are speaking to

ENTIRE.Definition: whole or complete, with nothing missing

ANALYZE.Definition: to study or examine something in detail in order to discover or understand more about it

VOCABULARY.Definition: all the words that exist in a particular language or subject

REINVENT YOURSELF.Definition: to change your job and/or the way you look and behave so that you seem very different

AIN'T.Definition: am not : are not : is not : have not : has not

FIT IN.Definition: to feel that you belong to a particular group and are accepted by that group

CROWD.Definition: a large group of people who have gathered together; a crowd is also a group of people with similar interests

CLEARLY.Definition: used to show that you think something is obvious or certain

DO YOUR THING.Definition: to do what you want without worrying about what anyone else thinks of you

GET INTO.Definition: to become interested in an activity or subject, or start being involved in an activity

COMEDY.Definition: a movie, play, or book that is intentionally amusing either in its characters or its action

HOMELESS.Definition: people who do not have a home, usually because they are poor

KEY.Definition: the most important part of achieving something or explaining a situation

GRAMMATICALLY.Definition: in a way that relates to grammar or obeying the rules of grammar

ACCENT.Definition: the way in which people in a particular area, country, or social group pronounce words

DIALECT.Definition: a form of a language that people speak in a particular part of a country, containing some different words and grammar, etc.

BREAK IT DOWN.Definition: to divide something into smaller parts

TRANSCRIPT.Definition: a complete written copy of spoken or written words

KIND OF.Definition: in a way that approximates: more or less

TAKE UP.Definition: to accept or adopt as one's own

WAY OF LIFE.Definition: an important activity, job, etc., that affects all parts of someone's life

ADOPT.Definition: to choose someone or something or take something as your own

ACCOUNTANT.Definition: someone who keeps or examines the records of money received, paid, and owed by a company or person

DEGREE.Definition: a course of study at a college or university, or the qualification given to a student after he or she has completed his or her studies

PATH.Definition: a way of life, conduct, or thought

PROFESSION.Definition: a principal calling, vocation, or employment

THUS.Definition: because of this or that: hence, consequently

CONFUSING.Definition: something that is confusing makes you feel confused because it is difficult to understand

CONTEXT.Definition: the situation within which something exists or happens, and that can help explain it

OBLIGATED.Definition: feeling that you owe someone something because you are grateful for what they have done for you

EMBODY.Definition: to represent a quality or an idea exactly

FIGURATIVELY.Definition: in a way that uses words and phrases with a more imaginative meaning than usual

MAJORITY.Definition: the larger number or part of something

PAY ATTENTION.Definition: to watch, listen to, or think about something carefully

PATTERNS.Definition: a particular way in which something is done, is organized, or happens

BASIS.Definition: the way things happen, or are done or organized

POINT OUT.Definition: to talk about or mention (something that one thinks is important)

PRONUNCIATION.Definition: the way in which a word or letter is said, or said correctly, or the way in which a language is spoken

TYPICALLY.Definition: used when you are giving an average or usual example of a particular thing

STANDARD.Definition: usual rather than special, especially when thought of as being correct or acceptable

RECOGNIZE.Definition: to know what something is because you have seen it before, or because you have heard or read about it

INTENDED.Definition: to have as a plan or purpose

DESTINED.Definition: controlled by fate, and not by humans

YOU GOT THIS.Definition: used to tell someone that you believe they can or will succeed in dealing with something

PRESSURE.Definition: a difficult situation that makes you feel worried or unhappy

TECHNICALLY.Definition: according to an exact understanding of rules, facts, etc.

IMAGINE.Definition: to believe that something is probably true

FANCY.Definition: of particular excellence; executed with technical skill and style

HIT ROCK BOTTOM.Definition: to reach the lowest point possible

BOTTOM OF THE BARREL.Definition: the lowest possible condition, level, etc.

PROGRESS.Definition: a forward or onward movement (as to an objective or to a goal)

REFERENCING.Definition: to refer to someone or something

POINT.Definition: a particular time or stage reached in a process

DESTINATION.Definition: the place where someone is going or where something is being sent or taken

ORIGIN.Definition: the beginning or cause of something

FOR THE SAKE OF.Definition: because of, or for the purpose of something

RELATIVELY.Definition: in comparison with other similar things or with what you expect

METAPHORICALLY.Definition: relating to or using metaphors (= expressions that describe a person or object by referring to something that is considered to have similar characteristics)

PHRASAL VERB.Definition: a phrase that consists of a verb with a preposition or adverb or both, the meaning of which is different from the meaning of its separate parts

PARENT.Definition: to raise a child as their parent

INTERRUPTIONS.Definition: an occasion when someone or something stops something from happening for a short period

INSPIRED.Definition: to make someone feel that they want to do something and can do it

STRONGLY.Definition: very much or in a very serious way

ENCOURAGE.Definition: to talk or behave in a way that gives someone confidence to do something
